The standards created by the cabinet shall address the following:
Qualifications of providers of court-mandated domestic violence offender treatment services which shall include appropriate requirements for degree, experience, training, and continuing education;
Procedures for application by providers to receive certification which shall include methods of appeal if certification is denied, and sanctions for noncompliance with the standards which may include revocation of certification;
Admittance and discharge criteria for domestic violence offenders to enter court-mandated treatment services provided pursuant to this section;
Written protocols for referral by a court to certified providers and for progress reports to be made to the court by providers;
Contracts for domestic violence offenders to sign prior to entering court-ordered treatment services provided pursuant to this section. The contract shall specify that certified providers may contact the victims of the offender if the victim chooses to be contacted. The contract shall authorize the provider to release information regarding the offender's progress in treatment to the court, victims, probation and parole officers, and other individuals authorized by the court to receive the information;
Written procedures in compliance with KRS 202A.400, 209.030, and 620.030;
Payment protocols which require the offender to pay the actual cost for any court-mandated evaluation or treatment pursuant to this section, subject to the offender's ability to pay; and
Other provisions which shall further the availability and quality of court-mandated domestic violence offender services.

Any person certified under this section shall submit quarterly to the cabinet:
Demographic information and clinical characteristics on offenders served;
Number of offenders admitted into treatment and discharge conditions;
Total clinical services provided to offenders; and
Other information as required by administrative regulation.
